Module org.monarchinitiative.phenol.annotations
Package org.monarchinitiative.phenol.annotations.base.temporal

Interface TemporalInterval

All Known Subinterfaces:
Age, AgeRange
All Known Implementing Classes:
HpoOnset
public interface TemporalInterval
TemporalInterval is a pair of PointInTimes start() and end() where start() starts at or before end().

  • Method Details

    • gestationalPeriod

      static TemporalInterval gestationalPeriod()
      Provide TemporalInterval to represent the span of the gestational lifetime. The TemporalInterval is delimited by PointInTime.lastMenstrualPeriod() and PointInTime.birth().

      Note that length of the gestational lifetime is Integer.MAX_VALUE

      Returns:
      the TemporalInterval representing the gestational lifetime

    • postnatalPeriod

      static TemporalInterval postnatalPeriod()
      Provide TemporalInterval to represent the span of the postnatal lifetime. The TemporalInterval is delimited by PointInTime.birth() ()} and PointInTime.openEnd().

      Note that the postnatal lifetime is half-open, hence the length is Integer.MAX_VALUE.

      Returns:
      the TemporalInterval representing the postnatal lifetime

    • of

      static TemporalInterval of(PointInTime start, PointInTime end)
      Create a TemporalInterval using start and end. The start must not be after end.
      Parameters:
      start - non-null start
      end - non-null end
      Returns:
      a TemporalInterval
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if start is after end

    • open

      static TemporalInterval open()
      Returns:
      an open TemporalInterval; an instance where both isStartOpen() isEndOpen() is true.

    • openStart

      static TemporalInterval openStart(PointInTime end)
      Create a TemporalInterval with an open start.
      Parameters:
      end - PointInTime to be used as an end. The end can be open.
      Returns:
      a TemporalInterval with an open start if end is closed, or an open TemporalInterval if end is open.

    • openEnd

      static TemporalInterval openEnd(PointInTime start)
      Create a TemporalInterval with an open end.
      Parameters:
      start - PointInTime to be used as a start. The start can be open.
      Returns:
      a TemporalInterval with an open end if start is closed, or an open TemporalInterval if start is open.

    • length

      default int length()
      Get the number of days spanned by this TemporalInterval.

      Note: the length of a half-open or fully-open interval, or an interval with endpoints located on different timelines (e.g. gestationalPeriod()) is equal to Integer.MAX_VALUE.

      Returns:
      the number of days.

    • isEmpty

      default boolean isEmpty()
      Returns:
      true if length() is equal to 0.

      default TemporalOverlapType temporalOverlapType(TemporalInterval other)
      Get TemporalOverlapType for TemporalIntervals this and other.

      Note: the method returns TemporalOverlapType.CONTAINED_IN if this and other are equal.

    • contains

    • compare

      static int compare(TemporalInterval x, TemporalInterval y)
      A comparator-like function for default sorting of TemporalInterval instances.

      In the comparison, the start() is compared first. In case of a tie, instances are compared based on end().
